Right, I previously had the logic to recompute the Cluster when the partition was removed, but took that out since it made the partition count inaccurate. Now we are only removing partitions when the topic subscription has changed.

I'll add the Cluster refresh back.

How about I change `MetadataCache#removePartitionInfo(TopicPartition)` to `MetadataCache#removePartitionInfosForTopic(String)` so we only remove an entire topic rather than a single partition. This should avoid the situation where the partition count in Cluster is inaccurate. That would change the behavior to be like:

```
metadata.setTopics(Collections.singletonList("topic-2"));

// now metadata for other topics is unavailable
assertNull(metadata.fetch().partition(tp));
assertNull(metadata.fetch().partitionCountForTopic("topic-1"));
assertFalse(metadata.partitionInfoIfCurrent(tp).isPresent());
```

